<h1>Problem 1062 - 2021 ELMO, P2 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(n > 1\) be an integer and let \(a_1, a_2, \ldots, a_n\) be integers such that \(n \mid a_i-i\) for all integers \(1 \leq i \leq n\). Prove there exists an infinite sequence \(b_1,b_2, \ldots\) such that
<ul><li>\(b_k\in\{a_1,a_2,\ldots, a_n\}\) for all positive integers \(k\), and</li><li>\(\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}{b_k}/{n^k}\) is an integer.</li></ul></p>
